    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-01-06T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-01-06T05:00:00-05:00" n="273"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6531/296: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-01-06T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 6, 1936—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 6—9:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. Your No. 1, January 4, 3 p.m. I have done as instructed in last paragraph. Mr.
                        Suvich<note n="3" xml:id="d273fn3">Fulvio Suvich, Under Secretary of State
                        in Italian Ministry for Foreign Affairs.</note> said he had also received a
                    cable from Rosso in that sense.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
